  "text": "The deduced protein of 18.7 kDa is similar to the iron-sulfur cluster containing hydrogenase subunits. The easily recognizable two ferredoxin-type CxxCxxCxxxCP motifs suggested the presence of two [4Fe-4S] clusters, thus MhyG seems to represent an electron transfer subunit. The corresponding subunits of other hydrogenases like HycF in E. coli, were proposed to play a role in the electron transport [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] .",
